### 6. Stimulus Target Integration

When using Stimulus controllers, IDs complement `data-[controller]-target` attributes:

```html
<!-- Dropdown with both Stimulus targets and IDs -->
<div data-controller="dropdown" id="user-menu-dropdown-container">
  <!-- Stimulus target for controller logic -->
  <button data-action="dropdown#toggle" 
          data-dropdown-target="button"
          id="user-menu-toggle-button"
          aria-haspopup="true"
          aria-expanded="false">
    Menu
  </button>
  
  <!-- Stimulus target with ID for external access -->
  <div data-dropdown-target="menu"
       class="hidden"
       id="user-menu-dropdown-menu">
    <a href="/profile" id="user-profile-link">Profile</a>
    <a href="/settings" id="user-settings-link">Settings</a>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Modal with Stimulus -->
<div data-controller="modal" id="delete-confirmation-modal">
  <div data-modal-target="overlay" 
       id="delete-modal-overlay"
       data-action="click->modal#close"></div>
  <div data-modal-target="content" id="delete-modal-content">
    <button data-action="modal#close" 
            id="delete-modal-close-button"
            aria-label="Close">×</button>
    <div id="delete-modal-body">
      <!-- Content -->
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Autosave form with Stimulus -->
<form data-controller="autosave"
      data-autosave-url-value="/articles/1"
      id="article-edit-form">
  <input data-autosave-target="field"
         id="article-title-input"
         type="text">
  <textarea data-autosave-target="field"
            id="article-body-textarea"></textarea>
  <div data-autosave-target="status" id="autosave-status">
    Saved
  </div>
</form>
```

**Stimulus + ID Guidelines:**
- Use `data-[controller]-target` for Stimulus controller logic
- Add IDs when:
  - Element needs to be accessed outside the Stimulus controller
  - Form labels need association
  - Deep linking/anchors required
  - Testing needs stable selectors
  - Multiple controllers interact with same element
- ID format remains consistent: `[context]-[element]-[type]`
- Prefer Stimulus targets for internal controller logic
- Use IDs for external access and debugging

